The UFC needs these weight classes
 
The UFC currently has 9 weight classes spanning fron 115 pounds all the way to 265 pounds.
 
But there are a few weight classes in the sport of mixed martial arts that the UFC doesn‚Äôt have.
 
First is atomweight, which refers to 105 pounds, and while it may sound strange, adding this weight class to the women‚Äôs lineup would give more women the chance to fight in the UFC and deepen the roster.
 
Next is Super lightweight, or 165 pounds, which is a weight class many UFC fighters and personalities have pushed for. It would give fighters who are too big for lightweight and too big for welterweight a fair shot at UFC gold without having to deplete themselves.
 
Super middleweight at 195 would also be great so fighters don‚Äôt have to cut all the way down to 185.
 
Next is cruiserweight, or 225 pounds because the range between 205 and 265 is too much for for many fighters who are more in-betweeners.
